to believe the document is more credible?"

00:48:17.750 --> 00:48:23.050 position:63%
&gt;&gt; Yes, you know, I think we always are
trying to be really cognizant of the way

00:48:23.050 --> 00:48:27.160
in which the wording of tasks
may influence students.

00:48:27.160 --> 00:48:30.320 position:73%
And we try certainly quite hard not to do that.

00:48:30.320 --> 00:48:35.030 position:58%
And one way that we do that is, we do
think-aloud interviews with students

00:48:35.030 --> 00:48:40.520 position:61%
where we sit down and ask them to think
out loud as they complete our tasks.

00:48:40.520 --> 00:48:45.130
And sometimes we find that, you
know, the students read the tasks

00:48:45.130 --> 00:48:47.190 position:69%
in a very different way than we intended it.

00:48:47.190 --> 00:48:49.450
And then we tweak it as a result.

00:48:49.450 --> 00:48:51.900
So, you know, our hope is
certainly that we don't want

00:48:51.900 --> 00:48:54.790 position:75%
to be influencing students one way or the other.

00:48:54.790 --> 00:48:57.140
But it's an ongoing process.

00:48:57.140 --> 00:49:03.980 position:56%
So it's possible, but our hope is
they're not unduly being influenced.

